      "id": 79520,
      "name": "Cesar Nunez",
      "username": "Cesar_Nunez",
      "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/c/e95f7d/{size}.png",
      "created_at": "2025-06-19T17:00:05.125Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Is there a way to create an outside workout base on a route where I can set each interval based on the route?</p>\n<p>For example, a 5 miles straight flat (grade 0%) route with a climb of 0.5 miles right on the middle with a grade of 5% where I want to climb in 100% my FTP and 90-95 cadence.</p>\n<p>I think I figure something out but need advise if I\u2019m doing it right.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>I create a route in Garmin Connect</li>\n<li>Exported the GPX file</li>\n<li>I created a new workout based on a route from that GPX</li>\n<li>TD shows the new workout intervals based on the file</li>\n</ul>\n<p>This the link to access this workout \u2192 <a href=\"https://app.trainerday.com/workouts/loop-diamond-lake\" class=\"inline-onebox\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Trainer Day</a></p>\n<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/original/2X/a/aac31acdd83a1350aa998e12fd6af013ee82e811.png\" data-download-href=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/aac31acdd83a1350aa998e12fd6af013ee82e811\" title=\"image\"><img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/a/aac31acdd83a1350aa998e12fd6af013ee82e811_2_690x368.png\" alt=\"image\" data-base62-sha1=\"omDb9rozirNATiBXqlaAnIn3fpL\" width=\"690\" height=\"368\" srcset=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/a/aac31acdd83a1350aa998e12fd6af013ee82e811_2_690x368.png, https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/a/aac31acdd83a1350aa998e12fd6af013ee82e811_2_1035x552.png 1.5x, https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/a/aac31acdd83a1350aa998e12fd6af013ee82e811_2_1380x736.png 2x\" data-dominant-color=\"E7E5E9\"><div class=\"meta\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">image</span><span class=\"informations\">1658\u00d7886 83.9 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>\n<p>From here I\u2019m lost, I don\u2019t know how TD figured the time for each interval and FTP%. Neither Type and Slope/BPM comes from.</p>\n<p>Actually, I checked the SLOPE &amp; HR TARGET and it shows the column with those values</p>\n<p>The other thing I noticed is when I saved the workout, TD shows the indoor, HR, and outdoor workout options; however, when I switch from indoor to outdoor I can see the intervals change</p>\n<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/original/2X/0/0eb87ccd42b7ea6b10f13db08ba0f4f1c3482399.png\" data-download-href=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/0eb87ccd42b7ea6b10f13db08ba0f4f1c3482399\" title=\"image\"><img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/0/0eb87ccd42b7ea6b10f13db08ba0f4f1c3482399_2_690x219.png\" alt=\"image\" data-base62-sha1=\"26dWJdwmrLsIdyx0UzG5kPLNfEB\" width=\"690\" height=\"219\" srcset=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/0/0eb87ccd42b7ea6b10f13db08ba0f4f1c3482399_2_690x219.png, https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/0/0eb87ccd42b7ea6b10f13db08ba0f4f1c3482399_2_1035x328.png 1.5x, https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/original/2X/0/0eb87ccd42b7ea6b10f13db08ba0f4f1c3482399.png 2x\" data-dominant-color=\"E0E4F0\"><div class=\"meta\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">image</span><span class=\"informations\">1109\u00d7353 14.7 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>\n<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/original/2X/1/1207a89c94354e7eeacce7ca0501011e61c282f8.png\" data-download-href=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/1207a89c94354e7eeacce7ca0501011e61c282f8\" title=\"image\"><img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/1/1207a89c94354e7eeacce7ca0501011e61c282f8_2_690x206.png\" alt=\"image\" data-base62-sha1=\"2zv0bDoyiUnXPHoOWXr5SGQE34Q\" width=\"690\" height=\"206\" srcset=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/1/1207a89c94354e7eeacce7ca0501011e61c282f8_2_690x206.png, https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/1/1207a89c94354e7eeacce7ca0501011e61c282f8_2_1035x309.png 1.5x, https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/original/2X/1/1207a89c94354e7eeacce7ca0501011e61c282f8.png 2x\" data-dominant-color=\"DDE0ED\"><div class=\"meta\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">image</span><span class=\"informations\">1043\u00d7312 14.5 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>\n<p>I wonder if I\u2019m doing something wrong, or TD isn\u2019t capable to create a outdoor workout base in a real route, where the intervals match the course gradient or distances, and then we can adjust the intervals to the targets we need to modify accordingly with our training plan</p>\n<p>If TD can do it, I\u2019d really appreciate your advise and give some lights to make right. It will be an excellent a powerful training tool for sure</p>",
