      "cooked": "<p>So we don\u2019t have any perfect solution for this, but really all you are talking about is specific power targets in specific places on  your route.  The best way to do this in general is to focus on the climbs or just a few key targets on the route.  Then use either our editor or in Garmin connect you can set specific distances and ours you can not.  But I would avoid distances and times completely and just use open ended which means you start the workout\u2026 When you get to your first climb you press the lap button and it will go to your target watts.</p>\n<p>See below how to do that in our tool<br>\n<div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/original/2X/2/20ff435fb429dac06823ee496f6e3a4fe4ba215a.png\" data-download-href=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/20ff435fb429dac06823ee496f6e3a4fe4ba215a\" title=\"image\"><img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/2/20ff435fb429dac06823ee496f6e3a4fe4ba215a_2_690x426.png\" alt=\"image\" data-base62-sha1=\"4HUb1OWE5w99jgQBO5dURrlgQZk\" width=\"690\" height=\"426\" srcset=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/2/20ff435fb429dac06823ee496f6e3a4fe4ba215a_2_690x426.png, https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/2/20ff435fb429dac06823ee496f6e3a4fe4ba215a_2_1035x639.png 1.5x, https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/2/20ff435fb429dac06823ee496f6e3a4fe4ba215a_2_1380x852.png 2x\" data-dominant-color=\"D5D7E2\"><div class=\"meta\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">image</span><span class=\"informations\">1536\u00d7950 49.9 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>\n<p>See below Garmin\u2019s workout creator.  You could use distances just for the climbs for example.  Or specific areas.<br>\n<div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/original/2X/9/94574a2cf0eea090ec58ccebd50608d2c37f1ad2.png\" data-download-href=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/94574a2cf0eea090ec58ccebd50608d2c37f1ad2\" title=\"image\"><img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/9/94574a2cf0eea090ec58ccebd50608d2c37f1ad2_2_690x433.png\" alt=\"image\" data-base62-sha1=\"lahGlDPSa9J4R9oBrL4VqDxo0Xo\" width=\"690\" height=\"433\" srcset=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/9/94574a2cf0eea090ec58ccebd50608d2c37f1ad2_2_690x433.png, https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/9/94574a2cf0eea090ec58ccebd50608d2c37f1ad2_2_1035x649.png 1.5x, https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/original/2X/9/94574a2cf0eea090ec58ccebd50608d2c37f1ad2.png 2x\" data-dominant-color=\"FAF9F9\"><div class=\"meta\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">image</span><span class=\"informations\">1330\u00d7836 36.8 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>\n<p>You can find the distance in ridewithgps workout creator for example.  But I am sure garmin route creator or any of them you can.</p>",
